  "prompt": "How do people with no common language communicate?",
  "response": "People with no common language can communicate through several methods:\n\n1. Non-verbal communication\n- Gestures\n- Facial expressions\n- Body language\n- Pointing\n- Pantomime/acting out actions\n- Drawing pictures\n- Using objects to demonstrate meaning\n\n2. Universal symbols\n- Mathematical symbols\n- Traffic signs\n- Basic pictographs\n- Numbers\n- Simple diagrams\n\n3. Context and environmental cues\n- Showing/demonstrating actions\n- Using physical objects\n- Indicating directions\n- Shared visual environment\n\n4. Basic technological tools\n- Translation apps\n- Online translation services\n- Gesture translation software\n- Picture-based communication apps\n\n5. Simplified language techniques\n- Speaking slowly and clearly\n- Using simple words\n- Basic repetition\n- Emphasizing key words\n- Using international words that might sound similar\n\n6. Physical/emotional communication\n- Tone of voice\n- Emotional expressions\n- Touch (with cultural sensitivity)\n- Shared emotional experiences\n\n7. Mathematical/scientific communication\n- Universal mathematical notation\n- Scientific symbols\n- Basic computational representations\n\nEach method has strengths and limitations, but humans are generally adaptable and creative in finding ways to understand each other.",
